    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-04T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-04T14:00:00-05:00" n="266"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d266">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3–3149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-04T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 4, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>426. Re Peiping’s 525 and 526, Mar 31. Emb authorized in its discretion
                    coordinate with MA,<note n="82" xml:id="d266fn82">Military Attaché.</note>
                        NA<note n="83" xml:id="d266fn83">Naval Attaché.</note> and ComNavWesPac<note
                        n="84" xml:id="d266fn84">Commander, U.S. Naval Forces, Western
                        Pacific.</note> in issuing categorical denial Commie charges US bombing
                    cruiser <hi rend="italic">Chungking</hi>. Emphasis shld be made on ridiculous
                    nature of charges and official statements Chinese air force describing action.
                    Rpt text any statement to Dept for use on VOA.<note n="85" xml:id="d266fn85"
                        >Voice of America.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
